---
title: Chimichurri Grilling Cheese Toasties with Caramelized Onion & Southwest Potato Wedges
description: Did you know you can grill cheese? And no, we don’t mean the melty diner sandwich—we’re talking about throwing a big hunk of cheese directly onto the heat so the outsides get beautifully charred while the insides get warm and soft. If you haven’t gathered yet, it’s one of our all-time favorite dairy creations. Here, you’ll dredge the cheese in Southwest spices, then sear in a hot pan for that delicious crust. It’s sandwiched between toasted potato buns with caramelized onion and a bright, creamy chimichurri sauce, then paired with spiced potato wedges for good measure. Being cheesy never tasted so good.
